gmd:abstract.gco:CharacterString:
The Geofabric Surface Cartography product provides a set of related feature classes to be used as the basis for the production of consistent hydrological cartographic maps. This product contains a geometric representation of the (major) surface water features of Australia (excluding external territories). Primarily, these are natural surface hydrology features but the product also contains some man-made features (notably reservoirs, canals and other hydrographic features).
This product contains 9 feature types, (CanalLine, Dam, HydroArea, HydroLine, HydroPoint, MappedNode, MappedStream, Sea, Structure, TerrainBreakLine, Waterbody and WaterPipeline)

gmd:purpose.gco:CharacterString: The product may be used for visualisation of surface hydrology within a GIS to support the selection of features for inclusion in cartographic map production.

gmd:statement.gco:CharacterString: Geofabric Surface Cartography is part of a suite of Geofabric products produced by the Australian Bureau of Meteorology. The geometry of this product is largely derived from AusHydro V1.0. It consists of water bodies such as swamps, reservoirs, lakes, etc as derived from GEODATA Version 3 (GEODATA 3), as well as the stream lines and stream lines connectors through water bodies. The feature class terminology for Geofabric Surface Cartography components is modified to distinguish them in terms of the product's underlying data model.
